==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aërial railway
<hw>A*⟦eum⟧`ri*al rail"way`</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A stretched wire or
rope elevated above the ground and forming a way along which a trolley
may travel, for conveying a load suspended from the trolley.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>An elevated cableway.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aerial sickness</ent>⟦br⟧
